\label{lem:dominated_neighborhood}
    Let $X$ be a simplicial complex, and $u$ and $v$ vertices of $X$ such that $v$ dominates $u$ in $G(X)$.
    Then $N[u]\setminus \{ v\}\subseteq \partial X$. Consequently, if $u$ is dominated by two distinct vertices $v,v'$, then $N[u] \subseteq \partial X$.
